<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/26 (Thu)How to stop bickering and nagging ? &amp;  How worried are you ?  (Host: William)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=346&amp;p=362#p362"><![CDATA[
12/26 (Thu)How to stop bickering and nagging ? &amp;  How worried are you ?  (Host: William)<br /><br />How to stop bickering and nagging ? <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/FHxFIRaAV54">https://youtu.be/FHxFIRaAV54</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. It's so annoying when you have to say the same thing over and over again. Why people like to nag ? <br />2. Will the nagging stop if you just do what you're asked of ? <br />3. Nagging is the desire to change other people. Can it be effective ? <br />4. No one like to be a nagger, but they often feel like they have no choice. Do you agree with it. <br />5. Do you have any tips to stop nagging ? <br />6. Nagging someone is one of the most toxic things you can do for a person self isteems, along with bullying. Do you agree with it ?<br /><br />----------------------------------------------<br />How worried are you ? <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/q1FQzNiA8vI">https://youtu.be/q1FQzNiA8vI</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Do you consider yourself to be a worrier ? <br />2. Do yo have a hard time controlling your worry ? <br />3. Do you worry to avoid bad things from happening ? <br />4. When you are stressed and worried, what do you tend to dream about at night ? <br />5. Are you worried about your life, what you will eat or about your body, what you will put on .<br />6. How can you change your thinking --worry is tutile, worry is fruitless and worry is inappropriate ? <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:20 p.m. Free talk<br />7:20 p.m. --7:50 p.m. First topic discussion<br />7:50 p.m. --8:15 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:15p.m.-- 8:45 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />8:45 p.m.-- 9:00 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Fri Dec 20, 2019 9:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
